{
  "texts": [
    "The problem, then, is to turn these pairwise preferences into a ranking of the label set L. To this end, different ranking procedures can be used.",
    "The simplest approach is to extend the (weighted) voting procedure that is often applied in pairwise classification: For each label λ i, a score",
    "is derived, where h i, j (x 0) = 1h j,i (x 0) for i > j, and then the labels are ordered according to these scores.",
    "Despite its simplicity, this ranking procedure has several appealing properties.",
    "Apart from its computational efficiency, it turned out to be relatively robust in practice, and, moreover, it possesses some provable optimality properties in the case where the Spearman distance (6) is used as an underlying loss function."
  ]
}